sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809330
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GAL promoter + YFP + SPtom70 + Toc34+ ADH1 terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BioBricks of Toc34_SPtom70 (K809324) is linked with GAL promoter and ADH1 terminator. When expressed in cytoplasm, The Toc34 will be directed on mitochondrial outer membrane, and the YFP can function as a reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All parts should be linked correctly without nonsense mutation and frameshift mutation

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: YFP_SPtom7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YFP is linked with signal peptide of Tom70, thus can be directed to mitochondrial outer membrane. It is used to test and signal peptide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Both parts should be linked correctly without frame shift and nonsense mutation

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Toc34
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Toc34 is a GTPase protein that functions as signal peptides receptor, N-terminally anchored at chloroplast outer membrane.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was synthesized according to the sequence exactly

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SPtom70
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the signal peptide of Tom70, which can direct N-terminally anchored protein to mitochondrial outer membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Rapaport, D. (2003). "Finding the right organelle." EMBO Rep 4(10): 948-952.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is synthesized according to the sequence found in datebase
